OL,3,CFirst monument for Britain's 'cruel'
OL,4,Cforced adoption scandal unveiled
OL,6,FSurvivors of Britain's forced adoption
OL,7,Fscandal have marked the first public
OL,8,Fmonument in the UK recognising the
OL,9,F"immense suffering" of unmarried
OL,10,Fmothers and their children for decades
OL,11,Fin post-war Britain.
OL,13,FThe unveiling at the former site of
OL,14,FRosemundy Mother and Baby Home - which
OL,15,Fis now a hotel - in St Agnes,
OL,16,FCornwall, was attended by mothers,
OL,17,Fadult adoptees and campaigners, some
OL,18,Fwhom had travelled across the country
OL,19,Fto mark the occasion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
