OL,6,FBetween 1949 and 1976, an estimated
OL,7,F200,000 women and girls were sent away
OL,8,Fto institutions run by the church and
OL,9,Fstate, which were places of shame and
OL,10,Fsecrecy, with many coerced into having
OL,11,Ftheir children adopted.
OL,13,FLyn Rodden was one of these women.
OL,15,FShe was 19, pregnant and had recently
OL,16,Fsplit up with her boyfriend when she
OL,17,Fwas sent to Rosemundy Home, with the
OL,18,Fbelief she would recieve support there.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
