OL,6,FRetracing her steps with ITV News, she
OL,7,Fdescribed how every Sunday she would
OL,8,Fbe "marched up the hill to church"
OL,9,Fwith the other mothers, who would all
OL,10,Fbe "dressed in tabards to show we were
OL,11,Funmarried".
OL,13,F"The villagers would shout things like
OL,14,F'whore' and 'prostitute' at us as we
OL,15,Fpassed by," she said.
OL,17,F"We weren't seen as human, dogs were
OL,18,Ftreated better than us. It was
OL,19,FDickensian. It was an evil place, no
OL,20,Fkindness, just punishment."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
